Description: Body sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; white slip; exterior: part of two painted bands of opposing crescents separated by two lines.
Curator's comments: Sherd possibly belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1888,0601.561a-n.
Bibliographic references: Johnston 1978 / Pottery from Naukratis: An Exhibition on the Occasion of the 11th International Congress of Classical Archaeology (no. 60)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.131)
